sentences.english: The magister has been kind enough to provide us with suitable gifts.
sentences.chinese: 總督已經很慷慨的爲我們準備了合適的禮物了。

sentences.english: At intervals formal receptions were held at the governor's mansion.
sentences.chinese: 總督府中不時舉行正式酒會。

sentences.english: The school had been opened only last year by the agent to the governor-general .
sentences.chinese: 這所學校是去年由英屬領地總督的代理人主持開幕的。

sentences.english: Dumeridian has been applied frequently to regulate immunology function for its controlling Yang.
sentences.chinese: 督脈因其“總督諸陽”調整免疫功能而多被使用。

sentences.chinese: 總督府，新南威爾士州悉尼，1837年。

sentences.english: They led the father and son to Gessler, the cruel governor.
sentences.chinese: 他們把泰勒父子領到殘暴的總督蓋勒面前。

sentences.english: Soon enough the magister was fast asleep, leaving Tyrion to brood alone.
sentences.chinese: 很快總督就睡着了，流下提利昂獨自沉思。

sentences.english: It was also the seat of the Chinese viceroy of the three Manchurian provinces.
sentences.chinese: 這也是東北三個省所在地的中國總督的。

sentences.english: The unscrupulous governor attempted to sabotage the Roon Colonial Games.
sentences.chinese: 這位不擇手段的總督企圖破壞魯恩殖民地運動會。

sentences.english: On my advice, the Governor General has agreed to prorogue Parliament.
sentences.chinese: 總督採納了我的建議，同意推遲國會。

sentences.english: Governor Koong placed great stock in the Games.
sentences.chinese: 孔總督在運動會里投了很多錢。

sentences.english: His Excellency entreats you by me.
Are these two known to you, magister?
sentences.chinese: 這兩個人你認識麼，總督？

sentences.english: Viceroys who were often no better than bandits.
sentences.chinese: 往往和盜匪無甚差別的總督大人們。

sentences.english: Beans were brought to the island in 1728 by the governor at that time.
sentences.chinese: 咖啡豆是於1728年被總督帶到島嶼上的。
